text.Taxonomy and naming:
Boronia crenulata was first formally described in 1807 by James Edward Smith and the description was published in Transactions of the Linnean Society of London. The specific epithet (crenulata) is derived from the Latin word crena meaning "a notch or rounded projection" referring to the teeth on the leaf margins.There are four subspecies:

Boronia crenulata subsp. crenulata;
Boronia crenulata subsp. obtusa;
Boronia crenulata subsp. viminea;
Boronia crenulata subsp. pubescens.
